{
  "body" : "Set against a {{background}} with a sense of absolute void, the composition features a striking silhouette where only the sharp, elegant edges of the face and shoulders are glowing with {{rim_light_color}} rim light. {{subject}}.\n\n— Subject ({{atmosphere}} mood) —\n{{subject}} The figure feels {{atmosphere}}, conveyed entirely through head pose, posture and the precise way the rim light traces the silhouette. No expressive facial muscles are needed; the whole emotion lives in the contour.\n\n— Eyewear (the visual anchor) —\nThe subject wears {{eyewear}}. The frames catch and reflect a soft, ethereal glow, providing the only warmth and the only specular reflection in the palette. The lenses pick up tiny fragments of the rim light as faint catchlights — they are the visual anchor that prevents the silhouette from becoming featureless.\n\n— Face visibility —\n{{face_visibility}}. The interior of the face stays in deep shadow, emphasizing anonymity and intrigue through intense cinematic lighting. Do NOT add fill light, do NOT lift the shadows in post — the darkness is the design.\n\n— Lighting design —\nA single hard rim light from behind / above-behind the subject carves the outline of the head, hairline, jawline, nose bridge, lips, ears and shoulders. The light wraps just enough to catch a few hair strands and the upper edge of the eyewear frame. Background light: zero. Fill light: zero. Specular highlights only on the metal frame and lens surface.\n\n— Color palette —\nMonochromatic dark base ({{background}}) + a single edge color ({{rim_light_color}}) + the warm reflective accent on the eyewear. The whole image lives within 5–10% luminance for ~85% of the pixels, with the remaining ~15% being the rim and the lens reflections.\n\n— Composition & framing —\n{{framing}}. Captured in {{aspect_ratio}} aspect ratio. Negative space dominates 60–70% of the frame, focusing the viewer's attention on the stark contrast and the subtle interplay of light and shadow.\n\n— Rendering quality —\nUltra high resolution photorealistic portrait, shot on a medium-format digital camera (Hasselblad H6D / Phase One feel), 85mm or 110mm prime lens at f/2.8, ISO 100, deep blacks with no banding, smooth tonal gradient on the rim, sharp microcontrast on hair strands and frame edges. Cinematic color grade in the spirit of Roger Deakins (Blade Runner 2049) and Bradford Young (Arrival): rich blacks, restrained highlights, surgical edge control.\n\n— Additional details —\n{{extra_notes}}\n\n— Strictly avoid —\n- Do NOT add fill light or ambient light on the face\n- Do NOT make the eyewear glow like LED — it should reflect, not emit\n- Do NOT show clear eye details unless face_visibility specifies\n- Do NOT use any background texture, gradient banding, dust particles or vignette artifacts\n- Do NOT render hair as a flat dark mass — keep individual highlighted strands along the rim\n- Do NOT clip the blacks (preserve subtle gradient in the deepest shadows)\n- Do NOT add lens flare, light leaks, or post-production glow effects\n- Do NOT add any text, watermark, logo, or graphic overlay\n\nKeywords: cinematic portrait, rim light silhouette, brown sunglasses, mysterious, anonymous, high contrast, low-key lighting, dark void background, editorial fashion, moody, photorealistic",
